      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:3:80:8",
      "text": [
        " ثَوَابُ الْمُؤْمِنِ مِنْ وَلَدِهِ إِذَا مَاتَ الْجَنَّةُ صَبَرَ أَوْ لَمْ يَصْبِرْ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, and Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Al Fazl Bin Shazaan, altogether from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Ibn Bukeyr, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The Rewards of the Believer when his child dies, is the Paradise, whether he is patient or is not patient’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "8. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father and Muhammad ibn Isma’il has narrated from al-Fadl ibn Shadhan all from ibn abu ‘Umayr from ibn Bukayr who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that the reward for a believing person for the death of his sons is paradise, whether he exercise patience or not.” "
        ]
      }
